Cyclist Tony Martin: May extend career
Time trial specialist Tony Martin is considering extending his career.
Frankfurt/Main - Seven time world champion time trialist Tony Martin can certainly see himself continuing his cycling career.
“At the moment I’m talking with the team to work out exactly how we can continue,” the 35-year old told the "Frankfurter Allgemeine Sonntagszeitung".
Martin is currently employed by Dutch team Jumbo-Visma and, prior to the coronavirus break, he had been thinking about ending his career after this year.
The negotiations with his team include discussing the number of race days, he said.
Plus other issues that would affect him as a father, he added.
After falling, he used to get up and his first thought was, “Get back on the bike quickly!
Now, as th father of a little girl, I think: what if?”.
Martin admitted that there are issues that he finds increasingly difficult.
“But it did me good, during the virus, to see what I’ve got from cycling and how much I enjoy it”.
The time trial specialist’s next race will be the Tour de l'Ain (5th to 9th August).
