Freital: Windberg Festival cancelled due to coronavirus
The Windberg Festival will not take place this year.
The city of Freital has cancelled the three-day festival that was planned for September.
In other years, over 30,000 people had visited this city festival.
“We have genuinely not made this decision lightly and, being aware of how financially tough it is for those involved, we were hoping up until the last minute,” explained Mayor Uwe Rumberg (independent).
“But ultimately, as the organizers, we are responsible for the health of several thousand people”.
Because if tens of thousands had poured into the festival area and the marquee, we wouldn’t have been able to comply with the virus rules on social distancing, hygiene regulations and contact tracing.
Or the restrictions would have been so severe that not much of the festival atmosphere would have remained.
The organization and monitoring costs would also have multiplied and been disproportionate.
Rumberg was consoled by thoughts of next year.
The city of Freital will then be celebrating its’ 100th birthday, with festivities including Winterberg Festival from 7th to 9th May 2021 and Saxons’ Day from 10th to 12th September 2021.
