“We are looking forward to being with you again next season,” says Carey.
The cancellation of the American races was met with criticism above all in Brazil: “For us, the cancellation is not surprising, but we cannot accept the reasons for this,” said Tamas Rohonyi, promoter of the Grand Prix in São Paulo.
The infection rates in the São Paulo region are much lower than in other regions in Brazil.
Some teams’ concerns of not wanting to drive in Brazil would also not justify a cancellation.
They are ready for the required safety measures.
